<DOCNO> AP900801-0003 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the president of the american bar association 
reported that 55000 cash given him by a client was stolen from a 
hotel safe deposit box 
stanley chauvin a louisville ky lawyer who heads the aba 
said he had put the money in a rented box at the hyatt regency 
hotel where he is staying during the groups annual convention 
chauvin 55 said he discovered the money missing when he 
checked the box tuesday night he declined to say how much money 
disappeared 
but hotel spokeswoman nancy ruth said chauvin reported 55000 
missing and added that the money was in 100 bills stashed in a 
cloth bag 
chauvin told police he had picked the money up from a client 
on the way from louisville lt kenneth bringe said wednesday 
he didnt want to go back to louisville to put the money in 
the bank so he brought it to chicago and stored it in the 
deposit box he said 
bringe said there was no obvious evidence that the box had been 
tampered with but police questioned employees took fingerprints 
and checked the boxs lock 
ms ruth said there are only two keys to the box a guard key 
for employees and one for the guest both keys must be used to open 
the boxes behind the hotels front desk 
she said an employee had unlocked the box tuesday night and left 
the room before chauvin realized the money was missing 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

