five years after a plague of locusts hit 
africa a congressional report says its still unclear whether the 
plague was stopped by a fouryear 275 million international 
pesticide attack or just by the weather 
a 130page report released tuesday by congress office of 
technology assessment failed to resolve whether the weather or the 
massive pesticide effort should get credit for stopping the plague 
in 1985 locusts and grasshoppers attacked 23 countries from 
portugal to tanzania and from iran to the atlantic in 1988 
hurricane gilbert blew fragments of locust swarms to the yucatan 
coast of mexico though apparently they did little damage there 
