<TEXT>
grossingers hotel and country club the 
borscht belt retreat that launched eddie fishers career and helped 
jack dempsey develop his punch will soon be little more than a 
summer memory 
the catskills hotel which entertained 100000 guests a year in 
its heyday in the 1940s and 50s probably will be sold off 
piecemeal to end years of financial trouble said barbara 
balliberstrauss its bankruptcy trustee 
the 812acre resort in the town of liberty has been empty since 
1986 when it was closed for a 30 million renovation and expansion 
project that never was completed 
before air conditioning and convenient air travel a getaway for 
hot tired new yorkers meant a twohour drive to the catskill 
mountains 
but like many resort areas close to big cities the catskills 
faded as other parts of the world became more accessible and an 
extended summer siesta became unfashionable grossingers went into 
a slide with other hotels in the region 
joe risitano 60 who has vacationed in the catskills since 
1948 was hired as a security guard at grossingers and said he 
spent tuesday turning away people curious to see the hotel 
a lot of people are saying their grandparents stayed here and 
always talked about it he said now they want to see it its 
nostalgia you know 
fisher who made his debut at grossingers 41 years ago and was 
discovered there as legend has it by eddie cantor returned to 
help kick off the facelift in 1986 which was halted in 1989 more 
than a dozen contractors filed liens of more than 87 million 
against the owners contending they had not been paid 
the owners a group of new york city investors had bought the 
resort from the grossinger family in 1985 
the financial trouble is a far cry from the heydy of 
grossingers and other resorts in the catskills known as the 
borscht belt for the jewish crowd that vacationed there and the 
jewish singers and comics who entertained them 
grossingers had it all a 27hole golf course ski slope 
indoor and outdoor pools and tennis courts post office shopping 
arcade two kosher kitchens and a 1500seat dining room 
dempsey rocky marciano ken norton and michael spinks trained 
there lucille ball performed at the resorts two nightclubs joel 
