seven styles of herring 
the resort was opened in 1914 by austrian immigrants selig and 
mahlke grossinger losing money the family sold it for 9 million 
in 1985 to grossingers associates an unrelated group of investors 
last december the owners filed for protection from creditors in 
us bankruptcy court under chapter 11 of the bankruptcy code 
balliberstrauss said the hotel and its contents likely will be 
liquidated under chapter 7 
what we plan to do is meet with lenders in order to determine 
the best approach to take balliberstrauss said 
in his the glory and the dream william manchester listed 
the first singles only weekend held at grossingers among the 
greater events of 1962 followed by john glenns spaceflight and 
the cuban missile crisis 
