<TEXT>
in the annals of usmongolia 
relations secretary of state james a baker iiis visit starting 
thursday will rank as relatively tame 
american adverturerbusinessmen were running car services 
between the chinese border and ulan bator then called urga as 
early as 1916 and were embroiled in smuggling kidnappings and 
shootouts 
their cadillacs and dodges were the first cars in this 
landlocked central asian nation whose very name for many americans 
epitomizes things remote exotic and dangerous 
the first official us envoy came in 1920 from beijing to 
evaluate a plea from mongolian princes for help in ousting their 
chinese overlords 
but when mongolian revolutionaries made their move in 1921 it 
was the soviet red army that helped starting a sevendecade 
alliance that sealed off mongolia from the west more effectively 
than geography 
one brief contact came in july 1944 the communist party 
newspaper unen recently reported when us vice president henry 
wallace stopped in ulan bator while traveling between china and the 
soviet city of irkutsk 
the united states and soviet union were world war ii allies and 
mongolian soldiers also were fighting the japanese 
unen said reporters were keen for their first look at an 
american 
but he was very ordinary the paper said he emerged 
without any hat dressed in a very light suit and without any tie 
wallace who like baker stayed three days met with 
thendictator marshal horloogiyn choybalsan visited museums took 
in a play and met mongolian horsemen whom he surprised with his 
knowledge of racehorses 
another contact came in the early 1960s after the united states 
stopped blocking mongolian entry into the united nations mongolia 
invited us supreme court justice william o douglas to visit and 
he gave lectures on the us legal system 
american hunters began arriving in 1967 starting up what has 
become a multimilliondollar safari industry for mongolia 
negotiations on establishing diplomatic relations failed 
however both in the early 1960s and in the late 1970s finally as 
the cold war thawed relations were established in 1987 
the united states sent its first resident ambassador in june 
even as the soviet union continued pulling its troops out a 
complete soviet troop withdrawal is scheduled for 1992 
but americans are still relatively rare in ulan bator which 
bears a heavy soviet stamp in its architecture food and consumer 
goods the cadillacs and dodges are long gone replaced by official 
fleets of boxy black berras from the soviet union 
ordinary mongolians said they were surprised to hear of bakers 
visit many people in washington were too despite its location 
between china and the soviet union mongolia is not key to american 
strategic planning 
one motive appears to be bakers interest in hunting he will 
spend two days on a private hunting and fishing expedition in the 
gobi desert 
us officials say baker also will sign a consular agreement and 
an agreement to send peace corps volunteers they are expected to 
start teaching english next year 
the two sides also are negotiating a general trade agreement 
mongolia is seeking mostfavorednation trade status from the 
united states which would entitle it to the lowest tariffs on its 
exports total trade between the countries last year was 16 
million 
baker also will meet with mongolias communist leaders and 
representatives of new opposition parties that contended in the 
countrys first free elections sunday 
nyamdoo the mongolian ambassador to washington said baker did 
not confirm his trip until the opposition dropped its threat to 
boycott the elections the state department said the visit serves 
to demonstrate our support for mongolias peaceful democratic 
reform process 
it is a subtle slap at neighboring china with whom the 
washington has halted most highlevel visits since the chinese army 
attacked prodemocracy protesters in beijing in june 1989 it would 
have been natural for baker to stop in beijing which is a main 
gateway to mongolia 
opposition activists say they hope to learn from the us 
democratic system they want us investment and development aid to 
reduce mongolias dependence on the soviets 
the mongolian government also wants trade investment and 
technology 
mongolia is ready to get anything he can give to us deputy 
foreign minister choinhor said jokingly monday 
american businessmen are slowly starting contacts 
the new yorkbased textile company amicale industries recently 
started a joint venture in mongolia to process camel hair 
exploration associates of houston is searching for oil and 
ringling brothers circus has signed up mongolian circus acts 
mongolian vodka is expected to appear in us stores next year 
one measure of mongolian interest in the united states came when 
a group of scholars founded the mongoliaus association in may 
gonchigdorj a founding member said 500 people showed up for the 
first meeting 
