del tufo of attempting to buy an indictment and said the call 
for a new panel was unscrupulous 
they shouldnt be playing politics with the grand jury 
system he said 
the victims father said he was disappointed but hopeful 
this is a sad day its three and a half months since my son 
was shot in the back for no reason pannell said 
but he said he had a message for the youth of teaneck chill 
out 
im willing to give america another chance for justice he 
said i feel justice will be served 
late tuesday community leaders counseled teaneck youths 
gathering behind the police station not to resort to violence 
try to be calm talk it out over the next few days said ted 
wells of the national association for the advancement of colored 
people he urged the gathering to trust the judicial process 
calling the empaneling of a second grand jury an extraordinary step 
if there was a scam theyd give no indictment shut up and 
bite the bullet he said 
a key question before the panel was whether pannell had raised 
his hands in the air and pleaded with police not to shoot as some 
witnesses said or whether he twice stopped and turned in a 
threatening way toward the officers 
officials close to the case say one crucial question is whether 
pannell was frisked by officer wayne blanco moments before he was 
shot according to the record of hackensack 
blanco said he frisked the teenager and warned spath about a 
gun he felt in pannells jacket according to the newspaper 
but teenagers with pannell said there was no frisking before 
the youngster ran and the man whose telephone call alerted police 
about a youth with a gun said he backed the youths accounts when 
he testified before the grand jury the paper said 
police said they recovered from pannells clothing a 
chromeplated athletic starter pistol that had been modified to 
fire live ammunition 
weve been praying for the pannell family all along and will 
continue to pray for the pannell family spath said at a news 
conference 
black leaders had demanded that a special prosecutor handle the 
case but instead it was transferred from bergen county to a state 
