suppression of opposition made his first public statement since 
rebels reached the citys suburbs more than a month ago doe 
reiterated he does not intend to surrender 
he said he would fight until the last soldiers in the liberian 
army die 
he spoke from the fortified israelibuilt presidential mansion 
under siege by rebel forces led by prince johnson 
the battles came a day after up to 600 civilian refugees were 
killed in a suburban st peters lutheran church compound 
witnesses said government troops who used cutlasses and bayonets 
in addition to bullets were to blame 
doe said rebels dressed as soldiers were responsible for the 
massacre 
i do not want to believe that the armed forces of liberia 
would just walk into a church and kill innocent people he said 
tuesday in an interview with the british broadcasting corp 
the victims were members of the gio and mano tribes from which 
the rebels get most of their support soldiers accused of the 
massacre were said by witnesses to belong to does krahn tribe 
in rome pope john paul ii today decried the massacres of 
civilians in liberia and appealed for an end to the fratricidal 
struggle in the african nation the appeal was the popes third 
since the fighting escalated 
