<DOCNO> AP900801-0100 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here are excerpts from recent editorials in newspapers in the 
united states and abroad 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
july 28 
the registerguard eugene ore on the income gap 
resentment of the rich is a recurrent theme of american 
politics it has fueled populist sentiment that rises angrily and 
then lies dormant for a while 
a new wave of such feeling may be sweeping toward the electoral 
beach today the reason is that during the 1980s in the united 
states the rich got considerably richer the poor got poorer and 
the majority in the middle treaded water 
a report confirming that common impression was issued by the 
center on budget and policy priorities based on data released by 
the congressional budget office 
the center concluded the combined incomes of the richest 
25 million americans now nearly equal the combined incomes of the 
100 million americans with the lowest incomes 
these developments have powerful implications for public policy 
and politics the clearest example of the former is the capital 
gains tax cut advocated by the bush administration 
the center says the data show clearly that the rich gained the 
most from the tax cuts approved during the reagan years and it 
calculates that 94 percent of the benefit from the proposed capital 
gains tax cut would go to the richest 20 percent of americans 
making the gap between the rich and the notrich wider than ever 
 
the facts of national income disparity cannot be glossed they 
represent a disturbing problem that needs to be addressed by all 
parties and factions not disguised or ignored 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
july 25 
philadelphia daily news on military spending 
its hard not to laugh at the pentagons idiocy 
consider the 99920 pair of pliers pratt and whitney managed to 
foist on the bluesuited dopes of the air force paying almost a 
grand for a pair of pliers after all is something curly larry 
and moe might do with their inheritance when pratt and whitney 
explains theyre multipurpose not only do they put the clips on 
but they take them off it goes somewhere peewee hermans 
imagination could not follow 
its funny that is until you realize whos been had until you 
realize that pratt and whitney set the price just 80 cents under 
the 1000 limit that would have required the air force to buy the 
damn thing from the people who actually made it instead of a 
greedy middleman take away that big score motive and the air 
force might have shlepped down to sears and bought it for 249 and 
gotten a lifetime warranty to boot 
you paid the difference funny huh 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
july 26 
the parkersburg wva news on the congressional mailing 
privileges 
one of the worst abuses of office regularly perpetrated on 
capitol hill is the use of taxpayersupported free 
congressional mailing privileges to send de facto campaign 
brochures to constituents among the worst offenders are freshman 
members of the house who use the franking privilege to put their 
names and usually their pictures before the voters this helps 
them build name recognition which is crucial to any election 
effort but is especially important to those seeking reelection 
an informal study by the washington post found that members of 
the house are urging some inventive ways to get around the few 
restrictions on franked mail members are limited to three 
massmailed newsletters but there is no limit on the number of 
notices for meetings that may be sent out nor is there any limit 
on mailings of less than 500 pieces 
well surprise surprise freshman house members and many of 
their more senior brethren as well have found an easy way around 
that one hold lots of meetings meetings that just happen to take 
place during the six months prior to elections and by all means 
dont rely on the local media to publicize these purely 
nonpolitical meetings with constituents no siree better tell them 
about it by postcard 
several times 
at a cost of about 13 cents per piece of bulk mail each 
massmailed town meeting notice newsletter to 225000 households in 
an average congressional district would cost the taxpayers 
29250 the post notes 
no wonder the house has a 98 percent reelection rate when an 
incumbent sends out three or four mass mailings a year he is 
taking a de facto 100000plus campaign contribution straight from 
taxpayers many of whom would not give him a dime if openly 
solicited it is difficult if not impossible for any challenger 
to overcome the bottomless and unprincipled pockets of incumbents 
who abuse their mailing privileges 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
july 31 
long beach calif press telegram on the louisiana abortion law 
veto 
antiabortionists in louisiana are helping to shape the future 
of international family planning more directly than you might ever 
imagine in france the maker of the abortion pill ru486 admits 
that drugs distribution has been slowed by fears of american 
opinion the result is that ru486 which has the promise of saving 
hundreds of thousands of womens lives each year has been kept 
away from countries desperate to have it 
in louisiana gov buddy roemer vetoed two excessively 
restrictive antiabortion bills passed by the state legislature 
this year the first long since gone permitted abortion only to 
save the mothers life the second expanded abortion to victims of 
incest and aggravated rape as long as the crime was reported to 
police and medical attention was sought within seven days such 
cruel and unusual conditions prompted roemers second veto 
in such a process an erroneous message is sent around the world 
that most americans are rabidly opposed to abortion indeed the 
german conglomerate that owns the french pharmaceutical firm that 
makes ru486 is so afraid of an american boycott that it has 
relegated international control of ru486 to the world health 
organization 
the feeble sensitivities of european industrialists no doubt 
give pleasure to many antiabortionists yet when 200000 women 
worldwide die for lack of a reliable lowcost lowrisk abortion 
procedure the efforts to make ru486 unavailable are in themselves 
inhumane 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

