noting that republicans have been hit with tough criticism for 
their package house budget committee chairman leon panetta said 
we didnt pledge that every time the republicans slit their 
wrists that we would slit ours 
the republican plan calls for increasing taxes on alcohol and 
limiting tax deductions on state and local taxes 
bush discusssed the budget impasse over coffee and donuts this 
morning with about 150 republican members of the house and senate 
bush vowed to veto spending bills and force congress to live 
with a sequester or deep automatic cuts if the lawmakers fail to 
come to terms on a plan to slash 500 billion from the deficit over 
the next five years gop leaders said 
gop lawmakers left the session declaring that bush was getting 
ready to go on the offensive unless the democrats offer their own 
version of a deficitreduction plan within 48 hours 
house republican whip newt gingrich said the first phase of 
the summit has collapsed 
indeed it appeared unlikely that serious bargaining would 
happen before september when the vacationing bush and congress 
both return to washington 
gingrich said bush indicated he was willing to stay in 
washington to get a budget agreement even though he is under 
pressure from his wife to join her at their kennebunkport retreat 
gingrich quoted bush as saying you know barbaras up at 
kennebunkport with two dogs one of them sick and with six 
grandkids and she needs me 
white house deputy press secretary roman popadiuk said bush in 
his meeting with republicans said we have been dealing with the 
democrats in good faith and we have a plan we are prepared to share 
with them when they present theirs they have not yet done so 
in contrast with gop lawmakers predictions that bush would get 
tough with the democrats popadiuk said merely that it was 
obvious that we are frustrated by this process that theres very 
little progress and of course the american people can judge for 
themselves on this issue 
i can expect the president to speak out but in what degree or 
in what shape form or manner i do not know popadiuk said 
lawmakers said bush told them he wants a budget plan from 
democrats by friday 
if that doesnt happen said house republican whip newt 
gingrich i think he may start getting tough in august i 
think the white house has been far more patient than i would be 
white house deputy press secretary alixe glen said you can 
assume that when the gop lawmakers go home they wont be shy about 
the footdragging weve seen by the democrats about finding a 
