<TEXT>
so far 1990 is just an average year for 
earthquakes the government said wednesday although the iranian 
quake in june was the deadliest in 14 years 
the us geological survey said the death toll in iran 
estimated at 50000 or more is the highest since a 1976 quake in 
china killed more than 250000 people 
overall there were 34 significant quakes in the first six 
months of 1990 that would be close to normal since there are on 
average 60 significant quakes in a typical year the agency said 
a significant quake is defined as one reaching 65 or higher on 
the richter scale or a lesser temblor causing significant 
casualties or damage 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released in an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
every increase of one whole number say from 55 to 65 
indicates a tenfold increase in ground motion 
the quake that struck iran measured 77 on the scale according 
to waverly person chief of the agencys national earthquake 
information service in golden colo 
that was the same magnitude as the deadly quake that hit the 
philippines on july 16 the death toll in that quake is still being 
calculated 
on feb 8 a quake measured at 66 injured at least 15 people in 
the philippines 1 died there in a quake on march 26 and a tremor 
on june 14 killed 4 people 
only one significant quake was recorded in the united states 
from january through june a magnitude 55 tremor that injured 38 
people and caused 10 million in damage in southern california on 
feb 28 
after iran the next deadliest quake in the first half of 1990 
was a magnitude 64 tremor in peru on may 30 which claimed 135 
lives 
on april 26 126 people were killed in a quake in china that 
measured 69 on the richter scale 
a tremor measured at 72 occurred may 20 in southern sudan 
because of the remoteness of the area casualty figures have not 
been confirmed survey officials said that is believed to be the 
strongest quake ever recorded in that country 
there were nine deaths reported in a may 30 quake in romania 
two people died in a may 5 quake in italy 
no injuries were reported but buildings were damaged when a 
quake shook parts of southern england on april 2 
overall person estimated that there are probably several 
million earthquakes annually most so small they are unnoticed 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

