<TEXT>
a small airliner carrying 30 people from armenia 
to the disputed territory of nagornokarabakh crashed in azerbaijan 
today soviet media reported no casualty report was immediately 
available 
the accident occurred in an area blanketed by dense fog but the 
cause of the crash was not known 
the wreckage of the aeroflot yakovlev40 was found in the agdam 
region of azerbaijan just east of nagornokarabakh and its 
capital stepanakert said the interfax news agency quoting a 
report to the armenian parliament 
the area is not on the planes route from the armenian capital 
yerevan to stepanakert but it could have been circling to enter 
its landing pattern 
air controllers lost contact with the plane this morning as it 
entered airspace controlled by stepanakert tass quoted the soviet 
state committee for air safety as saying stepanakert is 120 miles 
east of yerevan 
armenia and azerbaijan are locked in a bitter dispute over 
nagornokarabakh a remote mountainous area of azerbaijan 
populated largely by armenians hundreds of people have died in 
ethnic clashes in the past two years and thousands of armenians 
have organized into armed paramilitary units 
in this volatile atmosphere accidental deaths have spawned 
unfounded rumors of sabotage 
for example an explosion in a bus station in azerbaijan caused 
by leaking natural gas was reported widely as the result of a 
terrorist bomb 
the armenian parliament formed a fiveperson commission to 
investigate the catastrophe interfax said 
the search for the plane was hampered by thick fog the civil 
aviation ministry in moscow told tass civilian helicopters from 
azerbaijan were being used in the search the news agency said 
</TEXT>
