<TEXT>
merchant ships plucked 20 sailors from heavy 
waves wednesday after their cargo ship began to break up under the 
battering of hurricane bertha 350 miles off cape cod 
three crew members died and four were missing 
the crew of 27 abandoned the 593foot malteseregistered 
freighter corazon at 420 am 11 hours after reporting the ship 
was breaking up thirtyfoot waves whipped by wind gusting to 90 
mph had snapped its keel the equivalent of breaking its back 
soviet hong kong and norwegian merchant ships steamed to the 
stricken vessel to rescue crew members crowded in a lifeboat and a 
life raft us military aircraft coordinated from above 
she had fairly calm passage coming across the atlantic and 
bertha just swung right into her said charles aitcheson 
president of asca marine inc the ships new york agent 
obviously theyve tried to save as many as they could theyre 
all out there working hard to do it 
authorities did not know if the ship was leaking fuel or how 
much fuel was aboard 
hurricane bertha churned on toward canadas maritime provinces 
carrying 75 mph wind but was expected to weaken a swimmer in 
florida drowned tuesday in rough water attributed to the hurricane 
the corazon was carrying more than 25000 tons of cement bound 
from greece to new york and the load likely contributed to its 
damage said coast guard lt jg rodney gadsden 
we know it came apart in heavy seas he said we dont 
know if it was a structural problem or not it just happened 
because of the weather conditions 
by midmorning the corazons bow was submerged and its stern was 
standing clear of the water 350 miles southsouthwest of cape cod 
said coast guard petty officer anthony l whitehead 
one crew member apparently fell into the water when the crew 
members boarded the lifeboat and life raft whitehead said that 
sailor was pulled from the water dead by the russian trawler vympel 
four hours after they left their ship the 13 crew members on 
the lifeboat were taken aboard the soviet merchant ship leonid 
leonidov whitehead said 
but efforts to save the life rafts occupants went less 
smoothly the vympel attempted to rescue what was reported to be 12 
sailors aboard the raft whitehead said but the raft was pulled 
into the trawlers screw propeller and rudder area and six or 
seven sailors were pitched into the ocean 
the five remaining aboard the life raft were later pulled to 
safety two more life rafts were put out and three people were 
seen apparently in one of them gadsden said 
more precise accounting was unavailable but by afternoon the 
coast guard reported 20 sailors recovered alive three dead and 
four unaccounted for one survivor was reported injured 
