<TEXT>
more than 100 romanian intellectuals 
appealed wednesday for the release of jailed student leader marian 
munteanu and protesters gathered for the second straight day in a 
downtown square to demand his freedom 
the intellectuals appeal published in the independent daily 
romania libera said munteanus only crime was believing in 
democracy 
meanwhile president ion iliescu issued a statement urging the 
government to propose ways of eliminating tension and 
confrontation and calming the political climate 
iliescu a former highranking communist official who broke with 
ousted dictator nicolae ceausescu reiterated that he has 
completely disassociated himself from communist ideology 
iliescu and his national salvation front won mays multiparty 
elections 
he did not mention munteanu and dozens of other government 
opponents who have been jailed since midjune 
munteanu was one of the primary leaders of a 53day 
anticommunist rally in downtown university square that blocked the 
capitals main thoroughfare until it was violently broken up by 
police in midjune 
munteanu was badly beaten by progovernment miners who 
responding to an appeal for help from iliescu rampaged through the 
capital for several days beating intellectuals and others deemed 
government opponents munteanu was hospitalized and then detained 
the intellectuals statement charged that romania continues to 
be ruled by communists who have abandoned the ideology of 
communism but not its methods using terror and lies and 
hunting down intellectuals who oppose them 
the statement appealed for international support for the jailed 
activists 
its signatories included expatriate playwright eugene ionesco 
honorary writers union president stefan augustin doinas honorary 
romania libera editorinchief octavian paler and other members of 
the opposition intellectual group for social dialogue 
also wednesday several dozen protesters gathered in university 
square where they roped off an area and declared it a 
neocommunist free zone 
opposition activists use the term neocommunist to refer to 
iliescu and other national salvation front members who belonged to 
the nowdisbanded communist party the national salvation front 
emerged during the december revolution that overthrew ceausescu a 
communist hardliner 
the protesters held a placard demanding the release of munteanu 
and other jailed government opponents 
several policemen looked on but did not interfere on tuesday a 
scuffle broke out between demonstrators and a police officer after 
police tried to remove the ropes put up by the protesters 
