embarrassment they have faced ever since details of the 
administrations 54 billion package of spending cuts and tax 
increases emerged last week 
included in the plan are higher taxes on alcohol and a reduction 
in the deductibility of state and local income taxes both of 
which have drawn gop fire 
you can assume that when the gop lawmakers go home they wont 
be shy about the footdragging weve seen by the democrats about 
finding a credible solution to the budget deficit said white 
house spokeswoman alixe glen 
but democrats argued that a month of partisan warfare would 
accomplish little 
if we want to beat each other around politically were not 
going to come to an agreement and the public will take it out on 
both of us said panetta 
