most country clubs discriminate against women and restrict 
when they can play ms martin said wednesday as hard as it is 
to understand its really very simple to many men golf isnt a 
game its a disease that doesnt incorporate women 
ms martin who launched her own financial management firm after 
retiring from the insurance business said she smarted under the 
longmeadow country clubs restrictions for 25 years she filed the 
complaint only after trying unsuccessfully for six years to get the 
clubs board of governors to ease its restrictions on women 
as a younger woman you rationalize that making a squawk could 
hurt your business and back off she said im 65 ive lived a 
good life and gotten though a lot of different types of 
discrimination at this time in my life i have to face up to facts 
