philip jones griffiths a photographer who spent 
three years covering the vietnam war took a trip down memory lane 
last year but he did it the hard way on remnants of the ho chi 
minh trail 
when he first saw what once had been north vietnams famous 
muchbombed main supply route south he suffered a bit of 
