<TEXT>
computer giant ibm today said it will form a new 
subsidiary for its us typewriter keyboard and some printer 
businesses and intends the buyout firm clayton amp dubilier inc to 
become the units majority owner 
an announcement released from the armonk ny headquarters of 
international business machines corp said a plan is being studied 
to include the remainder of its worldwide information products 
business in the alliance with clayton amp dubilier 
the announcement didnt contain any financial details of the 
planned arrangements with clayton amp dubilier published reports 
have estimated that a buyout of the ibm businesses could cost about 
25 billion 
ibm spokesman glenn rossman said negotiations on a final 
agreement are expected to conclude by the end of the year until 
then no information will be disclosed on how much clayton amp 
dubilier will pay ibm or what size stake it will acquire he said 
wall street took the announcement in stride because there has 
been widespread publicity about ibms possible intention to 
reconfigure itself ibm stock gained 12 cents to 11187 in early 
trading on the new york stock exchange 
the new us company made up mainly of ibms information 
products business operations in lexington ky and boulder colo 
is expected to reduce the current work force by 1200 by the end 
of the year the company will have 3500 to 4000 employees ibm 
said 
ibm vice president marvin l mann will become the chief 
executive officer of the new company 
mann said making the information products operation a 
standalone business will enable it to concentrate its resources on 
expanding sales 
we intend to increase our investment on advertising and 
promotion greatly improve our dealer support programs and 
incorporate a sales force with information products as its only 
priority he said 
steps are being taken to assure that employees are treated 
fairly he said 
clayton amp dubilier chairman martin h dubilier said our 
intention would be to build on ibms reputation for quality and 
performance while developing more aggressive longterm growth 
strategies for new business 
clayton amp dubilier has had experience in businesses at the low 
end of technology since the firm was formed in 1978 it has made 
15 acquisitions with combined sales of 75 billion 
the new yorkbased buyout firm has made it a policy to avoid 
unfriendly maneuvers preferring to work in partnership with the 
management of the businesses it acquires 
ibm said it will maintain an equity holding in the new company 
the corporation will continue to market selected printer products 
made by the new company under the ibm name and will provide service 
for all printers 
the new company will provide typewriters intermediate and 
personal printers and supplies with the ibm logo through authorized 
dealers and other channels in the united states 
the work force reductions envisioned for the new company will be 
accomplished through a program of voluntary resignation and early 
retirement 
eligible employees in lexington will be offered the opportunity 
to resign retire or begin a fiveyear preretirement leave with 
incentive payments ibm said 
rossman said the program will be consistent with ibms 
longstanding policies regarding work force reduction 
the formation of the new company is part of ibms strategy to 
sharpen its focus to concentrate on its computer and software 
business 
ibm chairman john f akers said the action further advances 
ibms transformation and puts the information products division 
into a better position to grow in the future 
the new company will enable us to reduce overhead and more 
efficiently allocate our resources to strengthen both the 
subsidiary and ibm as a whole akers said 
