place its typewriter keyboard and certain printer operations into 
a new company in which it will retain a minority interest 
a firm specializing in buyouts clayton amp dubilier inc will 
acquire the majority stake in the new firm 
executives of international business machines corp and clayton 
amp dubilier said in interviews that negotiations on a final 
agreement are expected to conclude by the end of the year until 
then they said no information will be disclosed on how much 
clayton amp dubilier will pay ibm or what size stake it will acquire 
industry analysts have estimated that the businesses would be 
worth 25 billion to 3 billion 
the preliminary agreement calls for the new company to include 
the us portions of ibms information products business 
eventually the rest of the worldwide operation will be melded into 
the alliance with clayton amp dubilier said ibm vice president 
marvin l mann who will become the companys chief executive 
officer 
mann said in an interview that the companys businesses made up 
largely of ibm facilities in lexington ky and boulder colo 
will do better on their own than they would remaining within ibm 
under ibm this business has not had the highest of 
priorities he said ibm is less in the business of selling 
products and more in the business of selling solutions and total 
systems 
traditional typewriters have been elbowed out of offices by 
fancier machines capable of a broader range of functions noted 
barbara otto spokeswoman for the clevelandbased group 9 to 5 
national association of working women 
but mann said there still is money to be made in typewriters 
supplying products like typing elements for the vast number of ibm 
selectric and other machines already in offices is lucrative 
the typewriter business is not a growing business but its a 
profitable business and its still quite a substantial business in 
size he said 
and the new company will go beyond typewriters it will 
manufacture and supply keyboards for ibm and other companies 
workstations it will develop and market intermediate and personal 
printers and supplies mann said the printer and keyboard business 
is expanding rapidly 
the ibm offspring would rank within the top 200 of the fortune 
500 list of the countrys largest corporations based on annual 
revenue mann said 
wall street took the announcement in stride because there has 
been widespread publicity about ibms intention to reconfigure 
itself ibm stock added 12 cents closing at 11162 a share on 
the new york stock exchange 
steps are being taken to assure that employees are treated 
fairly mann said 
the new company is expected to reduce its work force by 1200 
with 3500 to 4000 employees by the end of the year including 
operations outside the united states the company would have 5000 
employees 
the anticipated job cuts will be accomplished through a program 
of voluntary resignation and early retirement eligible employees 
in lexington will be offered the opportunity to resign retire or 
begin a fiveyear preretirement leave with incentive payments 
ibm said the program will be consistent with its longstanding 
full employment policy of no layoffs since the mid1980s when 
growth in the computer industry began to slow ibm has pared its 
payroll through plant consolidations and voluntary early 
retirements 
the buyout firm figuring in ibms plans has had experience in 
lowerend technology businesses since it was formed in 1978 
clayton amp dubelier has acquired 15 businesses with combined sales 
of 75 billion 
the new yorkbased firm has made it a practice to avoid 
unfriendly maneuvers preferring to work in partnership with the 
management of the businesses it acquires 
chairman martin h dubilier said substantial investments will be 
made in the ibm company to broaden its product line bolster 
marketing efforts and strengthen the distribution network 
ibm will maintain an equity holding in the new company for an 
indefinite period of time said james j forese ibm vice president 
of finance 
he said the deal will not have a material impact on ibms 
earnings 
forese said the new company will continue to use the ibm logo 
for about three to five years before gradually making a transition 
to its own in seven to 10 years its products will carry a new 
logo 
formation of the new subsidiary is a key element of ibms 
strategy to stay on the cutting edge of the computer and software 
industry the company said 
it will fundamentally let us focus on our core business 
forese said when we looked at whats on our plate from a 
competitive standpoint we thought the information services 
business would be better off on its own 
</TEXT>
